Ace Nigerian music artist, Patoranking has announced the 10 inaugural recipients of his scholarship scheme in partnership with the African Leadership University (ALU). The 10 winners were selected after review of hundreds of applications from exceptional young people across the African continent. The Patoranking Scholars will be rewarded with 100 per cent paid tuition and a once in a lifetime opportunity to be part of the next generation of extraordinary African leaders and entrepreneurs at ALU. Among the scholarship recipients are two Nigerians, Chidera Nnadozie and Abdulmaleek Usman and other recipients from other African countries namely, Ghana, Tanzania, Zimbabwe, Uganda and Liberia. The rest of the recipients of the awards include Emmanuel Markwei, Hardness Range, Hanisani Nleya, Amos Kasumba and Maukafumbas Daramay